               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Khusraw va Shīrīn by Hātifī, d. 1520 or 21
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_244-item1">
                     <author key="person_79269545" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/79269545/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="standard">Hātifī, d. 1520 or 21</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">هاتفی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1408">Khusraw va Shīrīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_1408">خسرو وشيرين</title>
                     <note>F1a, stamp, the name entered in ink: Presented to the ROYAL ASIATIC SOCIETY by Lt Col. C.J. Doyle. A manuscript of sumptuous quality. A panel of illumination above the opening of the text, smaller ones on last two folios, headings in white on gold. Elaborate borders many based on stencils. Six miniatures and one tinted drawing. For the miniatures, marginal decoration and illumination see B.W. Robinson, Persian Paintings in the Collection of the Royal Asiatic Society, pp. 59-61. Entered in the Donations Register for 15 March 1834. No 6 in list of Persian MSS. Here, and for long afterwords, wrongly identified as the Khusrau wa Shirin of Nizami. The correct attribution is supplied in pencil by B.W. R[obinson] on the Library copy of Codrington.</note>
                     <incipit>Khudawanda bi-'ishqam zindagi dih</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Encyclopaedia of Islam, s.v. Hatifi.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, Suppt., p. 190.</bibl>
                        <bibl>C.f., Rieu, ii, pp. 652-3; Ethe, No 1398.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
